Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop both types of potato into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop @leek{1} and @baking potato{1} on a #large baking tray{} in a single layer, drizzle with oil and season with half the @dried thyme{1/4%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}, pop them on another #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{10%minutes} then remove from the oven.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice @echalion shallot{1/2}(peeled and thinly sliced). Trim the root and dark green leafy part from the leek (discard), halve the white part lengthways, thinly slice. Peel and grate @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Chop @tenderstem broccoli{150} in half widthways.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the leek and shallot and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Cook until they are soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Stir in the garlic, @ground cumin{2} and remaining @dried thyme{1/4%tsp}. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the lentils, @tomato passata{1} and @water for the lentils{100%ml}.

Stir the mixture, then add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} and bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the mixture has thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, remove them from your oven and mash on their tray with a #potato masher{} or #fork{} until broken up. Pop into a #mixing bowl{}.

Add the @Flora Original{10} to the potato and mash again to combine. Add a splash of @?milk{1%splash} (dairy free milk if you'd rather!) and half the parsley and mix together again until combined.

Taste the lentil mixture and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Stir in the roasted tomatoes into the lentils, then spoon the mixture it into an #ovenproof dish{}. Dollop the potato over the top, then spread out with a spoon to cover the lentils.

Use a fork to make ridges in the potato. Pop the pie on the top shelf of your oven to bake until the top is starting to crisp, ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wipe out the frying pan with some #kitchen paper{} and return to medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Add the broccoli and a splash of water and cover with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Steam-fry until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Divide the pie between your plates with the broccoli alongside. Finish with the remaining parsley. Enjoy!